{"article_id":"edfHxzzNBmfQtt1E","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Supreme Court delivered a mixed ruling on Monday","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that will allow President Trump to implement his travel ban against six Muslim majority nations","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"- but only for visitors","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"lacking ties to the United States .","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"The court ruled","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"that Trump may bar people from six majority Muslim countries","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"- Iran , Libya , Somalia , Sudan , Syria and Yemen -","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"if they have no `` bona fide '' relationship to the U.S.","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"Those","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that have established ties","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"will be allowed to continue entering the country ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"which covers the majority of visitors from those countries .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"More than 100,000 people legally entered the U.S. from the six countries in fiscal 2016 ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"which ended last Sept. 30 ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"according to State Department data .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Nearly 30,000 had immigrant visas ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"more than 25,000 arrived as refugees","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"and thousands more came on student , diplomatic and research visas","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"that require proof of a U.S. connection .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"All would be exempt from the ban under the court 's decision .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"The ruling means officials at the Department of Homeland Security and State will have to begin sorting through each application","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"submitted by travelers from the six targeted countries","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"to determine","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"if they have enough of a link to the U.S.","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"to enter .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"The justices provided several examples","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"to explain","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"who may enter the country :","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"If U.S. citizens claim close relatives from one of the targeted countries ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"they will be able to do so .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"If U.S. universities have accepted students from one of the targeted countries ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"the students will be able to enter the U.S.","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"and start their studies .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"If a U.S. business has given a job to a worker from one of the targeted countries ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"the worker will be able to do that job .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"\" In practical terms , this means","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"( the executive order )","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"may not be enforced against foreign nationals","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"who have a credible claim of a bona fide relationship with a person or entity in the United States , \"","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"the court wrote .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Supreme Court reinstates Trump 's travel ban ,","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"but only for some immigrants","depth":4},{"id":43,"text":"Two federal appeals courts had blocked the entire ban from going into effect ,","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"one saying","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"it violates constitutional protections for religion","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"and the other saying","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"it violates immigration law .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"The Supreme Court ruled","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"that a complete ban went too far ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"and it only blocked that part","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"affecting those with `` standing ''","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"to challenge Trump 's executive order in U.S. courts .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"The court said","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"Trump 's order may have violated the rights of U.S. citizens , universities and businesses","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"by preventing them from bringing in their relatives , students and employees from overseas .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"But the court concluded","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"that foreigners","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"who have no ties to the U.S.","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"can not argue , on their own ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"that constitutional protections apply to them .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"They 're not U.S. citizens , U.S. students or U.S. employees ,","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"so the protections","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"established in the Constitution","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"do not apply to them .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"The court ruled","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"that the administration 's main argument","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"- that the travel ban is needed","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"to improve vetting procedures","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"to stop would-be terrorists from entering the country -","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"is at its `` peak ''","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"when applied to foreigners","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"who have no ties to the U.S .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"`` The interest","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"in preserving national security","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"is , 'an urgent objective of the highest order , ' ''","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"the justices wrote .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"`` To prevent the Government from pursuing that objective","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"by enforcing ( the travel ban ) against foreign nationals","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"unconnected to the United States","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"would appreciably injure its interests ,","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"without alleviating obvious hardship to anyone else . ''","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"Justice Clarence Thomas issued a warning","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"about creating such an arrangement ,","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"warning","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"that a `` flood of litigation '' will soon follow","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"as the administration tries to walk the line","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"established by the Supreme Court .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"`` I fear","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"that the Court 's remedy will prove unworkable , ''","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Thomas wrote .","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"`` Today 's compromise will burden executive officials with the task","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"of deciding","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"- on peril of contempt -","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"whether individuals from the six affected nations","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"who wish to enter the United States","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"have a sufficient connection to a person or entity in this country . ''","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"The earliest","depth":3},{"id":98,"text":"the administration can begin enforcing the portions of the travel ban","depth":4},{"id":99,"text":"allowed by the Supreme Court","depth":4},{"id":100,"text":"is Thursday .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":201,"left":197,"right":200,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":143,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":141,"right":142,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":141,"left":120,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":112,"right":119,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":104,"right":111,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":0,"right":103,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":1,"right":102,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":102,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":111,"left":107,"right":110,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":107,"left":4,"right":106,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent"